title: In the Best of Families
description: Tony is threatened with criminal negligence after the son of a prominent lawyer hangs himself in his cell.

title: Do You See What I See
description: The commissioner sets out to trap a serial rapist in a Santa Claus mask who's been terrorizing the city.

title: The Poisoned Tree
description: Rachel refuses to believe Tony when he tells her that her school teacher colleague, Jim Hollister, is a child molester.

title: Nothing to Fear But Fear...
description: After receiving a pair of baffling death threats, Tony initiates around-the-clock surveillance of his unsuspecting family

title: A Matter of Life or Death: Part 1
A Matter of Life or Death: Part 2
description: Tony initiates a sweep to find a pair of missing cops; devises an ingenious way of keeping an habitually drunk driver off the road; and deftly handles an "extraterrestrial," all the while being scrutinized by a committee searching for a new police commissioner for New York City.

title: Behind the Storm Door
description: Tony is pursued by a woman he suspects is filing false complaints.

title: The Hatchet
description: Tony butts heads with both a tough cop who is overzealous in his handling of criminals, and a hard-nosed management consultant hired by the city in a cost-cutting effort.

title: Two Confessions
description: Tony is doubly stymied when identical twins both initially confess to the same murder, then, in a surprise about-face, accuse each other of the crime. Also, Arnie finds romance with a kindred soul, a phone-sex operator named Gloria.

title: The Commissioner's Ball
description: A serial killer has been mutilating the bodies of Eastbridge transients and homeless people -- and Tony begins to suspect the perpetrator's identity.

title: No Greater Gift
description: During the holiday season, Tony investigates the murder of an elderly woman allegedly killed in her home during a Christmas burglary; matches wits with a mugger, and defends a homeless woman who's been sleeping in the manger of a Holy Family creche.

title: The Fourth Man
description: After Commissioner Scali's friend and colleague, Chief of Detectives Irv Wallerstein, is struck down during a bloody encounter with hijackers, Tony becomes obsessed with finding the assailant!

title: Charlie Don't Surf
description: Vietnamese gangs threaten Eastbridge and Tony steps in to help.

title: Skeletons
description: A mugging triggers a woman's repressed mernosy of her brother's murder, which she witnessed as a child. The suspect, free for the past 35 years, is tracked to the unlikeliest of hiding places by Tony and a visiting friend, L.A. homicide detective Paulie Pentangeli.

title: The Wicked Flee
description: After seeing his mother killed by a stranger, a boy withdraws deep into himself, prompting a sympathetic Tony to step up his efforts to catch the murderer.

title: True Believers
description: The unwelcome appearance in Eastbridge of white supremacists leads to a murder, with the suspicion soon arising that one or more of Tony's associates may be implicated.

title: Officer April
description: After he shoots a woman in a drunken domestic squabble, Officer Kelly becomes the victim of a terrorization campaign.

title: Sex, Lies and Kerosene
description: Tony and Paulie investigate a puzzling arson case in which the husband of a beautiful woman appears to have been murdered.

title: Judgement Day
description: Tony winds up in one of his own jail cells when he runs afoul of an imperious judge who's hiding a fearsome secret.

title: Shoot the Breeze
description: Tony attempts to protect an informant from a mysterious hit man, while Stan Kelly enjoys a romantic encounter with a beautiful new Eastbridge arrival.

title: Video Vigilante
description: Tony is embarrassed, then enraged, as a publicity-seeking "video vigilante" metes out even more bizarre and harsh punishment to offenders.

title: The Puck Stops Here
description: Mike Cermak -- star high-school hockey player, recovering addict, and good friend of the Scali family - becomes a prime drug-ring suspect.

title: Adventures in the Skin Trade: Part 1
description: Commissioner, and expectant father, Tony Sciali finds his own life on the line after he infiltrates a New York pornographic teenage film ring

title: Adventures in the Skin Trade: Part 2
description: Commissioner Scali, kidnapped and seemingly destined for a sudden death, narrowly escapes his fate with the help of an unsuspected ally - porno movie producer Cyd Palmer.

title: Guns and Sons
description: Tony's son David is shocked when his friend Jason shoots Brad Harris, the school bully.

title: The Rolodex Madame
description: When Mary O'Grady, one of Eastbridge's most prominent and politically powerful socialities, is murdered, it is discovered she has been running a call girl service and, surprisingly, one name on her list of clients is Commissioner Scali!

title: The Witches of Eastbridge
description: As Halloween approaches, a heart is cut bom the body of a corpse at a funeral home. Because of a local history of tainted trick-or-treat candy, concerned Eastbridge parents pressure Tony to protect their children from the suspect, an eccentric recluse.

title: The Two Faces of Ed
description: Tony is tom when a series of life-threatening incidents occur in Eastbridge and the only link appears to be Ed Mize, an old, mild-mannered friend currently experiencing marital difficulties.

title: Escape
description: Tony, distraught when it appears that Phil Reid, one of his best men, may be targeted for revenge by a dangerous escaped convict, is further upset when he discovers that Phil's family harbors a dark secret.

title: A Time to Be Born
description: Rachel's in labor and about to give birth at any minute with only Cyd to support her because Tony is Literally out on a ledge trying to stop a troubled, older cop, who is a friend, from jumping.

title: The Witness
description: While grocery shopping, Rachel rum head-on into a robbery-murder suspect - and becomes the target of the killer's threats.

title: Sleep of the Just
description: There's a rapist attacking women. One of them gives a very good description of the man. Tony eventually finds him but learns he is a diplomat and has diplomatic immunity. Tony tries to get the Ambassador to sign his immunity away but it's not going to be easy. Tony learns that two of his patrolmen on the night shift are sleeping while on patrol which they attribute to being in court during the day. So, to prove them wrong, he goes on patrol during the night while doing administrative during the day. He also has to deal with the baby constantly crying.

title: The Frame
description: When a known mobster who claims to be retired moves to Eastbridge, Tony is concerned. He tries to get a dock permit but when he is rejected, the son of the man who decides that is framed for a crime he didn't commit. Obviously, the mobster framed him to get his father to change his mind. But Tony tries to prove his son's innocence so he doesn't have to give in.

title: Stoned
description: Tony's new car is stolen. He later is informed that a mental patient named Arlo Manno has escaped from a mental hospital and he wants to do some things that could endanger people like flying a plane, perform surgery and be a police officer. Sure enough he took a plane and crashed it. Trouble with finding him is that he is a virtual chameleon who assumes so many identities. Later Tony learns he might have kidney stones so he goes into the hospital.

title: The Heart Is a Lonely Sucker
description: Tony joins a video-dating service when he suspects one of his clients is a murderous thief. Also, Stan tries to protect Carmela from a clairvoyant's case.

title: The Sharp Pinch
description: Commissioner Scali and his team of officers pull out all stops as they try to beat the clock in a desperate search for the kidnapper of a very sick baby.

title: Dead Cadet's Society
description: Tony suspects foul play when a member of a commando-like squad of elite prep school students --

title: Family Business
description: When Nick Colette, the hot-headed son of "retired" mobster Tommy Colette, joins forces with his father, Eastbridge's crime troubles start.

title: Out of Business
description: Following the death of his gangster son in a police shootout, mobster Tommy Colette vows to kill Tony Scali himself.

title: The Ides of March
description: One of Tony's men, Danny Nolan, goes ballistic when Joe Laird, the gun-wielding ex-husband of the woman Dan's been seeing, takes her hostage.

title: Blue Flu
description: When the majority of Tony's officers stage a sick-out in the wake of a wage dispute, Eastbridge becomes an open city for crime.

title: Eastbridge Boulevard
description: Stella Stevens guest stars as a reclusive former movie queen - and one of Tony's all-time film favorites - who is implicated in the real-life murder of her lover.

title: Sight Unseen
description: Tony sets out to trap a serial rapist whose victims are young blind women Meanwhile, Rachel makes a surprising investment in art.

title: Anti-Commish
description: When a mysterious caller advises Tony that he is going to be his "partner" and do the things Tony would like to do but can't, a number of Eastbridge drug dealers suddenly turn up dead.

title: Scali, P.I.
description: After Tony resigned so that he could move to where Rachel's job takes her. But she turned down the job. Tony goes to the mayor hoping to get his job back but she already hired someone else. Tony goes to work for a P.I. And when he gets an uneasy feeling from the guy who replaced him, Tony decides to investigate him much to the chagrin of the guy he works for.

title: Mansion
description: When a wealthy socialite is found dead and it appears to be murder, Tony investigates. Initially evidence points to her two spoiled children who spend their time partying. But Tony gets a feeling he should take a look at her husband. And when the butler who agrees with Tony is found dead, Tony tries to prove it.

roles.char: First Applicant for Chief of Detectives

title: In the Shadows of the Gallows
